[medium] src/composables/useAiDiagnostics.ts:104 (correctness)
loadMoreRuns reuses the same runsRequest/runsRequestError state as refreshRuns. When a pagination request fails, useAxios sets runsRequestError; the returned runsError computed then becomes non-null, and AiDiagnosticsView hides the already-loaded runs table behind v-if="!runsError" instead of preserving the list and showing only paginationError. This turns a load-more failure into a full runs failure.
Suggested fix: Use a separate useDataApi instance for pagination, or stop feeding the shared runsRequestError into the top-level runsError computed and rely on the explicit runsError ref for refresh failures. Ensure load-more failures only set paginationError and leave the existing runs visible.
Guidance: In src/composables/useAiDiagnostics.ts, prevent loadMoreRuns failures from affecting the exported top-level runsError. The current loadMoreRuns uses the same runsRequest/useDataApi error ref as refreshRuns, and AiDiagnosticsView.vue hides the runs table when runsError is non-null. Use a separate useDataApi instance for pagination, for example execute: runsPageRequest, isLoading only if needed, and error: paginationRequestError if you choose to expose it, then call runsPageRequest only from loadMoreRuns. Keep refreshRuns using runsRequest and keep the exported runsError computed tied only to explicit runsError.value plus the refresh request error. On loadMoreRuns catch, set only paginationError.value and leave runs.value and nextCursor.value unchanged unless the request succeeds. Do not clear runs.value on pagination failure, and do not make AiDiagnosticsView ignore runsError as a workaround.
